Get the images before, one for the logo and the bigger one

In the body:

<body class="bg-gray-100">
  <img src="/img/logo.svg" alt="Workcation"/>
</body>

--add more padding by putting the img into a div:

  <body class="bg-gray-100">
    <div class="px-8 py-12">
      <img src="/img/logo.svg" alt="Workcation"/>
    </div>
  </body>

Now, asign to the image an smaller height:

<img class="h-10" src="/img/logo.svg" alt="Workcation"/>

Add another image below that:
using rounded-lg and shadow-xl

<img class="mt-6 rounded-lg" src="/img/beach-work.jpg" alt="Workcation"/>

-Below the image create an h1

<h1>You can work from anywhere. Take advantage of it.</h1>

Later add some utilites to the h1:

<h1 class="mt-6 text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 leading-tight">
         You can work from anywhere. Take advantage of it.
</h1>

Give more empathis to the part Take advantage of it.

using an span tag

